The paper deals with compressed sensing, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also discusses the use of prior knowledge and partial recovery, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper derives an upper bound for a computationally simple thresholding estimator, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the number of samples needed for recovery, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA).
